#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:13
msgid ""
"Bouncer is an application to help you choose the correct firewall zone for "
"wireless connections. When you connect to a new network, a window opens "
"prompting you for what kind of network (eg home, public, work) it is. When "
"you choose the network type, it is associated with that network and "
"automatically used in the future."
msgstr ""
"Bouncer er et program, der hjælper dig med at vælge den rigtige firewall-"
"zone til trådløse forbindelser. Når du opretter forbindelse til et nyt "
"netværk, åbnes der et vindue, hvor du bliver bedt om at angive, hvilken type "
"netværk der er tale om (f.eks. hjemme, offentligt, arbejde). Når du har "
"valgt netværkstypen, knyttes den til det pågældende netværk og anvendes "
"automatisk fremover."

#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:14
msgid ""
"NetworkManager and firewalld are required. If you don't use those, you can't "
"use Bouncer. Fedora uses both by default. Other distributions may not."
msgstr ""
"NetworkManager og firewalld er påkrævet. Hvis du ikke bruger disse, kan du "
"ikke bruge Bouncer. Fedora bruger begge dele som standard. Det er ikke "
"sikkert, at andre distributioner gør det."

#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:15
msgid ""
"Additional setup is required after installation. See the applicable section "
"for your distribution. Once the setup is done, start Bouncer and confirm "
"your system is configured correctly. Then click the Monitor button to begin "
"using Bouncer. After that, it will start automatically when you log in."
msgstr ""
"Der kræves yderligere opsætning efter installationen. Se det relevante "
"afsnit for din distribution. Når opsætningen er færdig, skal du starte "
"Bouncer og kontrollere, at dit system er konfigureret korrekt. Klik derefter "
"på knappen »Overvåg« for at begynde at bruge Bouncer. Herefter starter "
"programmet automatisk, når du logger ind."

#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:16
msgid "Fedora"
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:18
msgid ""
"For Fedora, everything just works! Just start Bouncer to confirm, and click "
"the Monitor button to begin using Bouncer."
msgstr ""
"I Fedora fungerer alt bare! Start blot Bouncer for at tjekke det, og klik på "
"knappen »Overvåg« for at komme i gang med at bruge Bouncer."

#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:20
msgid "Ubuntu"
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:22
msgid "Uninstall ufw: <code>sudo apt remove ufw</code>"
msgstr "Afinstaller ufw: <code>sudo apt remove ufw</code>"

#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:23
#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:29
msgid "Install firewalld: <code>sudo apt install firewalld</code>"
msgstr "Installer firewalld: <code>sudo apt install firewalld</code>"

#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:24
#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:30
msgid ""
"By default, polkit is configured to not let regular users set the zone for a "
"connection. The simplest way to change this is to add users to the "
"<code>netdev</code> group (eg <code>usermod -a -G netdev justin</code>). "
"Alternatively, you can create a custom polkit rule for the "
"<code>org.freedesktop.NetworkManager.settings.modify.system</code> action "
"(how to create custom polkit rules is beyond the scope of this document and "
"is left as an exercise for the reader)."
msgstr ""
"Som standard er polkit konfigureret til ikke at give almindelige brugere "
"mulighed for at indstille zonen for en forbindelse. Den nemmeste måde at "
"ændre dette på er at tilføje brugere til gruppen <code>netdev</code> (dvs. "
"<code>usermod -a -G netdev justin</code>). Alternativt kan du oprette en "
"brugerdefineret polkit-regel for handlingen "
"<code>org.freedesktop.NetworkManager.settings.modify.system</code> (hvordan "
"man opretter brugerdefinerede polkit-regler ligger uden for dette dokuments "
"omfang og overlades som en øvelse til læseren)."

#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:25
#: data/io.github.justinrdonnelly.bouncer.metainfo.xml.in.in:31
msgid ""
"Start Bouncer and confirm your system is configured correctly. Then click "
"the Monitor button to begin using Bouncer."
msgstr ""
"Start Bouncer, og kontroller, at dit system er konfigureret korrekt. Klik "
"derefter på knappen »Overvåg« for at begynde at bruge Bouncer."

